.TH "NAVIGATIONACTIVATION.NAVIGATIONTYPE" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationActivation.navigationType \- NavigationActivation:
navigationType property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]navigationType\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigationActivation\f[R] interface contains a string indicating
the type of navigation.
.SH VALUE
A string representing the type of navigation the
\f[CR]NavigationActivation\f[R] relates to.
Possible values are:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]push\f[R]: A new location was navigated to, causing a new entry to
be pushed onto the history list.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]reload\f[R]: The \f[CR]NavigationActivation.entry\f[R] was
reloaded.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]replace\f[R]: The \f[CR]NavigationActivation.entry\f[R] was
replaced with a new history entry.
This new entry will reuse the same \f[CR]key\f[R], but be assigned a
different \f[CR]id\f[R].
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]traverse\f[R]: The browser navigated from one existing history
entry to another existing history entry.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
window.addEventListener(\(dqpageswap\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// For example, the page was hidden, or the navigation is cross\-document.\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (!event.viewTransition) \f[B]return\f[R];

  \f[I]// Skip the view transition for back/forward navigations.\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (event.activation.navigationType === \(dqtraverse\(dq) {
    event.viewTransition.skipTransition();
  }
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
Navigation API
.IP \(bu 2
View Transition API
